					<h3 class="work-header"><a href="http://s4.twbbs.org/album/">Flickr Photo Sets Viewer</a></h3>
					<div class="work-description">
						A site to browse my public photo sets in <a href="http://www.flickr.com">Flick</a> with its API support. The main goal of this tool is to provide a tool for quickly searching public photos grouped by sets. I have created a backend to perform query to flick and a simple javascript app for UI and communicate with backend. Here are its detail information:
						<p>
							<h4>Frontend</h4>
							<ul>
								<li>Backbone.js</li>
								<li>jQuery</li>
								<li>Bootstrap</li>
							</ul>
							<h4>Backend</h4>
							<ul>
								<li><a href="http://mojolicio.us/">Mojolicious</a> (Perl Web Framework)</li>
								<li><a href="http://search.cpan.org/dist/Flickr-API2/">Flickr::API2</a></li>
								<li><a href="http://s4.twbbs.org/tech_blog/blog/2014/02/10/flickr-api-for-accessing-photo-in-set/">Extension of Flickr::API2 for performing query of public photosets</a></li>
							</ul>
					</div>
